Method Detail

mxMain

public void mxMain(matrix.db.Context _context,
                   String... _args)
            throws IOException
Main method to dispatch between different plug-in methods.

Parameters:
_context - MX context
_args - packed arguments as string with following meaning in this order:
  • first argument are parameters defined from ParameterDef_mxJPO
  • name of the method which must be called from the dispatcher
  • arguments for the called method
Throws:
IOException - if returned values could not be written

prepareReturn

protected <T> Map<String,Object> prepareReturn(String _log,
                                               String _error,
                                               Exception _exception,
                                               T _values)
Packed the values to return in a map.

Type Parameters:
T - defines the Java type of the values
Parameters:
_log - log message
_error - error message
_exception - throws exception
_values - values itself
Returns:
arguments packed in a map

encode

protected final String encode(Map<String,?> _values)
                       throws IOException
Packs the parameters into a map (with prepareReturn(String, String, Exception, Object)) and encodes this map as string (in Base64).

Parameters:
_values - values itself
Returns:
packed return values including log etc. as string encoded
Throws:
IOException - if encoding failed
